comment_data.body: This is the implementation used in TypeInference.py. I am not quite sure why it was changed in https://github.com/cython/cython/commit/0b547d5cf87eed72039ee727deea6d9539ec1898. However I assume it should be the same in both implementations. This fixes #3787

             # Python strings, etc., while correctly falling back to an
             # object type when the base type cannot be handled.
 
-            self.mark_assignment(target, node.item)
+            self.mark_assignment(target, ExprNodes.IndexNode(
+                node.pos,
+                base=sequence,
+                index=ExprNodes.IntNode(target.pos, value='PY_SSIZE_T_MAX',

comment_data.body:
No need to employ hashing here.
```suggestion
                    elif function.name == 'enumerate' and len(sequence.args) in (1, 2):
```

```suggestion
    >>> for_infered_type_in_enumerate_unicode(unicode_abc)
    Py_ssize_t Py_UCS4
    'X'
    >>> for_infered_type_in_enumerate_unicode(unicode_ABC)
    Py_ssize_t Py_UCS4
    2
    >>> for_infered_type_in_enumerate_unicode(unicode_abc_null)
    Py_ssize_t Py_UCS4
    'X'
    >>> for_infered_type_in_enumerate_unicode(unicode_ABC_null)
    Py_ssize_t Py_UCS4
    4
```
